### Our Strategic Approach

**Differentiation:** Competitors list shades; we explain the selection logic — why a shade reads heritage vs. trendy, how undertone dictates which nude actually looks expensive on you, and what makes the same colour look cheap in one finish and wealthy in another. We also include the 2026 forward-look (chocolate browns evolving, oyster grey emerging, milky white fading) — something none of the older posts do.

**Structure Plan:** Organise by colour family (not vague categories) with a clear editorial principle anchoring each — not just "here are nudes," but "here's the exact quality that separates an old money nude from a plain one." Include a practical skin-tone guide that competitors skip. Close with a distinction section between old money and quiet luxury palettes.

**Tone Direction:** Confident, witty, specific — like a stylish friend who actually knows polish names. Mirrors ThePinkIssue's voice. British English throughout. No filler.

